ğŸ–¥ï¸ Display Manager Fix

Initially, the VM booted to a non-GUI terminal.
To restore the graphical login screen (LightDM):

sudo apt install lightdm -y
sudo systemctl enable lightdm
sudo systemctl start lightdm


âœ… After reboot, successfully logged into the XFCE desktop environment.

ğŸ’½ VirtualBox Guest Additions

Inserted Guest Additions ISO, mounted, and installed essential modules:

sudo apt install build-essential dkms linux-headers-$(uname -r) -y
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/cdrom
sudo mount /dev/cdrom /mnt/cdrom
cd /mnt/cdrom
sudo sh ./VBoxLinuxAdditions.run


Verification:

lsmod | grep vbox


Output confirmed vboxguest and vboxsf modules were active.
ğŸŸ¢ Clipboard and display resizing features worked as expected after reboot.

âš™ï¸ Performance Tuning

Adjusted VirtualBox resource settings for smooth operation:

Parameter	Setting
RAM	4 GB
CPU Cores	2
Video Memory	128 MB
Acceleration	3D Enabled
Clipboard	Bidirectional

These changes significantly improved responsiveness and graphics stability.

